<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>17100</anchor> <rss>jms-00BF.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>jms-00BF</addr>  <route>jms-00BF.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>23</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The role of interchange in <link href="jms-00B8.xml" type="local" title="String diagrams">diagrammatic reasoning</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>In a 2-category, interchange is strict; in particular, this means that vertical composition and horizontal composition commute strictly with each other. This is very useful for <link href="jms-00B8.xml" type="local" title="String diagrams">string diagrams</link>, but it is not strictly necessary. In a <link href="jms-00B8.xml" type="local" title="String diagrams">string diagram</link>, strict interchange means that 2-cells can be freely moved upward and downward; so if you want to use diagrammatic reasoning to study something in a structure that has only weak interchange, you need two things:</p><ol><li>The vertical position of a 2-cell is fixed.</li>
  <li>No two 2-cells should appear at the same vertical position.</li></ol><p>To move a 2-cell up or down is to insert an interchange cell. It is this principle that makes <link href="jms-00BG.xml" type="local" title=" homotopy.io"> homotopy.io</link> work.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>17101</anchor> <rss>jms-00BG.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>jms-00BG</addr>  <route>jms-00BG.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>23</day></date> <authors><author>Lukas Heidemann</author><author><link href="jamievicary.xml" type="local">Jamie Vicary</link></author><author>Nick Hu</author> </authors> <title> homotopy.io</title> <meta name="external">https://homotopy.io/</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter/> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>17102</anchor> <rss>jms-00B8.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>jms-00B8</addr>  <route>jms-00B8.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>String diagrams</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  
